                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-13T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 13, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>199. Your 240, December 13, 6 p.m., paragraph 4. Assuming that your proposed
                    action will be adequately coordinated as to substance and timing with indicated
                    action of the British Ambassador, the authorization which you suggest is given.
                    You should guard against the Japanese authorities gaining the impression that
                    the American Government is in any way associated with the proposal which the oil
                    companies have in contemplation. If you make to those authorities any reference
                    to the proposal, you should avoid any mention of the express substance thereof
                    and should make clear the nonassociation of your Government therewith.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
